# Backend Standards

## FastAPI + Lambda
- Mangum adapter wraps the FastAPI app for Lambda execution (`handler.py`)
- Keep handler entry points thin — delegate to service layer functions
- Cold start budget: <2s for API handlers; minimize top-level imports
- Use `/tmp` filesystem for transient data in Lambda (ephemeral, 512MB default)
- No global mutable state in Lambda handlers — each invocation may reuse or create a container

## Request/Response Validation
- Pydantic v2 models for all request bodies and response shapes
- Define models in `packages/contracts/`, import into route handlers
- Return consistent error response format: `{"error": str, "code": str, "detail": any}`
- Include `request_id` in all responses for tracing

## Error Handling
- Use `HTTPException` with typed error codes for expected errors
- Map domain exceptions to HTTP status codes in exception handlers
- Never expose internal error details to clients
- Log full stack traces server-side with structured logging
- Return 5xx for unexpected errors, 4xx for client errors

## Authentication
- `get_current_user` dependency injection on all protected routes
- Validate JWT tokens from Cognito — deny-by-default on empty/missing groups
- Never trust client-provided user IDs — extract from token claims
- Use middleware for auth, not per-handler logic
- OFFLINE mode returns a synthetic test user (no network call)

## Lambda Powertools
- Logger: structured JSON logs with correlation IDs (execution_id, tenant_id, request_id)
- Tracer: X-Ray active tracing on all Lambda functions
- Metrics: CloudWatch EMF custom metrics (latency, error rates, token usage)
- Graceful degradation: if Powertools not available (local dev), fall back to stdlib logging

## Mode-Aware Behavior
- Check `AppMode` via `get_current_mode()` before making external calls
- OFFLINE: use stubs, return mock data, skip all network calls
- LOCAL_LIVE: real AWS calls against dev resources
- PROD: full production behavior, never set locally without explicit override

## Dependency Injection
- `@lru_cache` singletons for expensive clients (DynamoDB, Bedrock, S3)
- `reset_for_testing()` clears all caches — call in test fixtures
- Declare dependencies via FastAPI `Depends()` for testability

## API Design
- Use RESTful conventions for CRUD endpoints
- Read config from Secrets Manager via pointer pattern
- CORS origins configurable via `API_CORS_ORIGINS` environment variable
